      "The hotel's defining operational choice is the room-to-suite ratio. Of 139 total rooms, 46 are suites, the highest proportion in London. The suite layouts, restored in the 2015 Oetker refurbishment, range from one-bedroom park-facing suites on the upper floors to the Royal Suite, a two-bedroom penthouse with a dedicated butler and a private dining room. Every guest is assigned a personal butler for the length of stay, a service included in the rate rather than charged separately. This model is closer to Singapore or Dubai hospitality than to the broader London category.",
      "The Lanesborough Club and Spa, opened as part of the 2015 refurbishment, is the largest hotel spa in the immediate Belgravia and Mayfair area at 18,000 square feet, with a 20-metre indoor pool, a dedicated Bastien Gonzalez pedicure studio, and treatment suites across three levels. The Lanesborough Grill, overseen by chef Shay Cooper, handles the dining; The Library Bar, which holds one of London's deepest cognac collections (including bottles dating from the 1770s), handles the post-dinner crowd.",
