      "The single restaurant, CUT at 45 Park Lane, is the London outpost of Wolfgang Puck's American steakhouse CUT (the original in Beverly Hills opened in 2006). It operates as a standalone destination restaurant with its own entrance on Park Lane and attracts a separate clientele from the hotel. CUT specifically targets the high-spending international-visitor steakhouse market, which is a different register from the Michelin-starred Alain Ducasse room at The Dorchester. Bar 45, adjacent to CUT, runs in the same American-steakhouse register.",
      "The rooms, at an average of 60 square metres including a separate living area, are larger than equivalent categories at The Dorchester or the Mayfair grand hotels. Bathrooms are particularly generous. The design vocabulary is Art Deco contemporary: fluted walnut, Macassar ebony, polished metals, limited ornament. This is a restrained space rather than a theatrical one, which separates it deliberately from The Dorchester's more gilded interiors.",
